Google willÂ increase the price of YouTube TV to $40 per month for new subscribers. Good news for existing subscribers is that they still pay the original price of $35 per month. YouTube TV offers cable-free live TV, where subscribers can watch on mobile, tablet or computer, and smart TVs. The service includes content from over 50 networks, including ABC, CBS, FOX, and NBC. YouTube TV also features local sports networks from NBC Sports and FOX Sports. A subscription comes with six accounts per household, each with their own recommendations and personal DVR.